WEBVTT

00:00.561 --> 00:02.477
(man)
Previously on <i>Defiance...</i>

00:02.530 --> 00:04.396
I see a bright light.

00:04.398 --> 00:06.114
It's a man...

00:06.150 --> 00:07.816
with a powerful flashlight.

00:07.868 --> 00:10.619
(man)
Amanda, you're mine.

00:10.654 --> 00:14.072
The man who raped me.

00:14.074 --> 00:17.075
I was living in New York

00:17.127 --> 00:19.828
working as an entry clerk
at E-Rep headquarters.

00:19.880 --> 00:22.581
Why are you telling me
all this?

00:22.583 --> 00:25.000
I didn't want you to think
you're alone.

00:26.220 --> 00:28.420
We received a message
from Datak and Stahma.

00:28.455 --> 00:29.421
Good news, I hope.

00:29.456 --> 00:30.756
They were successful in planting

00:30.808 --> 00:33.508
the shrill-infested weapons
in the local armory.

00:34.762 --> 00:37.846
The town's entire gun supply
was destroyed.

00:37.898 --> 00:40.315
What does that madman want?

00:40.351 --> 00:44.536
He wants us to blow up
the St. Louis Arch.

00:48.475 --> 00:50.525
(Amanda)
People of Defiance,

00:50.578 --> 00:53.528
our darkest hour has passed.

00:53.581 --> 00:55.914
The lights are finally
back on.

00:55.950 --> 00:58.617
Thanks to our Omec friends,
the mines are open,

00:58.669 --> 01:01.753
and the gulanite
is flowing at a rapid pace.

01:01.789 --> 01:04.489
Slowly but surely,
we're getting back on our feet.

01:04.525 --> 01:06.041
'Cause when we're
up against the wall,

01:06.093 --> 01:08.694
when many of us
had just about lost hope,

01:08.729 --> 01:10.629
we persevered,

01:10.631 --> 01:12.965
standing beside each other.

01:12.967 --> 01:15.467
Always remember
who we are.

01:15.519 --> 01:18.437
We are free.
We are proud.

01:18.472 --> 01:21.139
We are Defiance.

01:23.143 --> 01:24.977
I can't speak
for the rest of you, Defiance,

01:25.029 --> 01:28.280
but I'm inspired.

01:28.315 --> 01:31.984
Here's some old-world grunge
going out to my man Alak Tarr,

01:31.986 --> 01:33.235
wherever you are.

01:33.287 --> 01:34.987
I notice you didn't tell
the town we were

01:35.039 --> 01:36.989
free, proud,
and defenseless.

01:37.041 --> 01:38.824
No need
to start a panic.

01:38.876 --> 01:41.159
Shrill destroyed
every weapon in our armory.

01:41.211 --> 01:42.327
I don't know about you,
but I'm feeling

01:42.329 --> 01:43.328
pretty damn panicked.

01:43.380 --> 01:46.331
[rock music]

01:46.383 --> 01:54.389
♪ ♪

01:57.478 --> 02:00.262
I think I got something here.

02:02.266 --> 02:05.817
Amanda, we've been going
through the old E-Rep files.

02:05.853 --> 02:07.436
I think I might have a line
on where we can

02:07.488 --> 02:08.937
find some weapons.

02:08.989 --> 02:10.989
[explosion]

02:12.526 --> 02:15.527
[crowd screaming]

02:17.000 --> 02:23.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:55.152 --> 02:58.320
[screams]

02:58.372 --> 03:00.655
(Rahm)
My fellow Votans,

03:00.708 --> 03:03.742
I am Commander General
Rahm Tak

03:03.794 --> 03:05.827
of the Votanis Collective.

03:05.879 --> 03:08.330
Today's a special day.

03:08.382 --> 03:11.249
Today is a day
of celebration.

03:11.301 --> 03:14.336
- I have shown you mercy.
- Hologram.

03:14.388 --> 03:16.922
(Rahm) I have come here today
to liberate you.

03:16.924 --> 03:19.307
You three, hey,
check the Arch for casualties.

03:19.343 --> 03:21.426
He's gotta be projecting
from somewhere close.

03:21.428 --> 03:25.097
You still have your homes.

03:25.149 --> 03:26.982
You still have your lives.

03:27.017 --> 03:31.937
But the continued survival
of Defiance is in your hands.

03:31.939 --> 03:35.323
I am an honest man.

03:35.359 --> 03:40.045
Far more honest
than your human mayor.

03:40.080 --> 03:41.947
My spies have informed me

03:41.999 --> 03:44.032
that all the weapons
in your armory

03:44.084 --> 03:45.584
have been rendered useless,

03:45.619 --> 03:47.702
a fact Amanda Rosewater
has kept from you.

03:47.755 --> 03:50.172
- Nolan, shut this down!
- Working on it.

03:50.207 --> 03:53.125
Like all pink-meat humans,

03:53.127 --> 03:55.210
she's a liar.

03:55.262 --> 03:57.462
I am coming to your town.

03:57.514 --> 03:59.881
Votans of Defiance,

03:59.933 --> 04:02.067
I make you this promise:

04:02.102 --> 04:04.269
your life will be spared

04:04.304 --> 04:06.638
if you surrender,

04:06.690 --> 04:08.974
but for those of you
who side with the humans,

04:09.026 --> 04:11.143
there will be no mercy.

04:21.321 --> 04:24.322
[dramatic music]

04:24.324 --> 04:25.128
♪ ♪

04:25.199 --> 04:30.199
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

04:32.416 --> 04:35.000
(Nolan) The Arch is only
the first salvo.

04:35.052 --> 04:37.502
Hitting back will require
weapons and lots of them.

04:37.504 --> 04:39.721
We may find them here.

04:39.756 --> 04:42.808
Station Arrowhead.
300 miles north.

04:42.843 --> 04:45.811
An EMC black site,
built during the Pale Wars

04:45.846 --> 04:48.013
and been sealed up tight
ever since the '20s.

04:48.015 --> 04:50.348
How do we know it hasn't
already been found, looted?

04:50.400 --> 04:52.067
We don't, but look
at the manifest.

04:52.102 --> 04:53.518
Automatic weapons, explosives,

04:53.520 --> 04:55.153
medical,
everything we could hope for.

04:55.189 --> 04:58.406
And if we drove all night, we
could be there by mid-morning.

04:58.442 --> 05:00.442
- This is heavy firepower.
- Mm-hmm.

05:00.494 --> 05:02.527
Worth rolling the dice.

05:02.529 --> 05:03.745
I'm riding shotgun.

05:03.780 --> 05:05.280
You heard the lady.
Pack a bag.

05:05.332 --> 05:07.415
Wheels up at sundown.

05:07.451 --> 05:10.001
- Not you, you're benched.
- Come on.

05:10.037 --> 05:11.419
- Benched.
- They blew up the Arch.

05:11.455 --> 05:12.754
- Don't care.
- Nolan!

05:12.789 --> 05:14.122
You're gonna stay here
with Berlin.

05:14.174 --> 05:15.874
You're gonna figure out
who planted those explosives.

05:15.876 --> 05:19.344
And you two, you're gonna work
together on this.

05:19.379 --> 05:20.879
You hear me?

05:20.881 --> 05:23.882
[jazz music]

05:23.884 --> 05:28.822
♪ ♪

05:28.823 --> 05:30.273
_

05:30.274 --> 05:31.389
You know how
everyone says that

05:31.441 --> 05:34.693
Buddy Rich is
the best drummer?

05:34.728 --> 05:36.228
I like Gene Krupa better.

05:36.230 --> 05:39.531
Krupa, yes.
<i>Sing, Sing, Sing.</i>

05:39.566 --> 05:41.032
Wonderful beat.

05:41.068 --> 05:43.318
A despicable species,
the humans,

05:43.370 --> 05:44.819
but they do have rhythm.

05:44.872 --> 05:47.122
General, sir.

05:47.157 --> 05:49.157
Sir, I have an update
on Defiance.

05:51.078 --> 05:53.628
Datak and Stahma
have destroyed the Arch.

05:54.882 --> 05:57.582
Ha! Excellent!

05:59.336 --> 06:00.585
And the hologram?

06:00.637 --> 06:02.337
The entire town saw it.

06:03.507 --> 06:05.724
Don't look so gloomy, Alak.

06:05.759 --> 06:07.475
Thanks to
your resourceful parents,

06:07.511 --> 06:08.927
you live to see
another day.

06:08.929 --> 06:12.314
(Bebe) But, sir,
there is one more thing.

06:14.568 --> 06:16.935
Speak freely.

06:16.987 --> 06:18.653
There are two Omec
in Defiance.

06:18.689 --> 06:21.106
One male, one female.

06:21.408 --> 06:22.857
_

06:22.910 --> 06:24.509
The Omec?

06:24.544 --> 06:25.994
Like from back on Votan?
Aren't they...

06:26.029 --> 06:27.579
Quiet!

06:28.916 --> 06:31.333
I've consulted
with my Indogene brothers,

06:31.368 --> 06:33.551
and we're fairly certain
that the male

06:33.587 --> 06:35.837
is Eksu Tsuroz T'evgin.

06:35.872 --> 06:38.290
He's a prominent figure
in Omec culture.

06:38.342 --> 06:41.259
Scientist, inventor,
politician,

06:41.295 --> 06:43.929
and war hero.

06:43.964 --> 06:47.515
Well, why isn't
this glorious renaissance man

06:47.551 --> 06:52.387
back home, dead, in space
with the rest of the enchanters?

06:52.439 --> 06:54.806
Our long-range scans
indicate that he has a ship.

06:54.858 --> 06:56.891
It's in orbit,
hovering above Defiance.

06:56.944 --> 06:58.026
A warship?

06:58.061 --> 06:59.878
We're not sure.

06:59.913 --> 07:02.147
Its power signature,
however, is very low.

07:02.199 --> 07:03.982
It's in need of repair.

07:03.984 --> 07:06.618
They need gulanite.
That's why they're in Defiance.

07:06.653 --> 07:08.903
A fully functional
Omec warship

07:08.956 --> 07:11.690
could destroy
the entire Votanis Collective.

07:11.725 --> 07:14.909
Eksu Tsuroz T'evgin
needs to die.

07:14.962 --> 07:16.828
Send word
to Datak and Stahma.

07:16.880 --> 07:21.166
Tell them I need it done
immediately.

07:21.218 --> 07:23.168
(Stahma) What he's demanding
is reckless.

07:23.170 --> 07:25.170
We must refuse
this order.

07:25.172 --> 07:26.638
That's not an option,
and you know it.

07:26.673 --> 07:28.340
It's too soon
after the Arch.

07:28.342 --> 07:30.342
The entire town's
on high alert.

07:30.394 --> 07:31.893
Rahm Tak is going
to get us caught.

07:31.928 --> 07:34.012
It's a risk
we have to take.

07:35.821 --> 07:37.120
Stahma...

07:37.133 --> 07:39.279
_

07:40.754 --> 07:42.687
What?

07:42.739 --> 07:44.606
Out with it.

07:44.658 --> 07:47.692
I've given this
a great deal of thought.

07:50.280 --> 07:53.531
I don't believe Rahm Tak
will ever release Alak alive.

07:53.533 --> 07:55.116
How can you say that?

07:55.168 --> 07:57.786
He married a human girl.

07:57.838 --> 07:59.537
Rahm Tak won't let that
go unpunished.

07:59.589 --> 08:01.840
No, you're wrong.
Rahm and I shared an oath.

08:01.875 --> 08:03.258
I looked him in the eye.

08:03.293 --> 08:04.376
Rahm Tak's eyes are empty!

08:04.378 --> 08:06.678
Even if you're right,
it changes nothing.

08:06.713 --> 08:08.246
Killing the Omec
buys us time.

08:08.281 --> 08:09.881
- Time for what?
- I don't know!

08:09.933 --> 08:12.217
Time to...
to-to think,

08:12.269 --> 08:15.103
to come up with some sort
of counter-strategy.

08:15.138 --> 08:18.473
What other choice
do we have?

08:18.525 --> 08:20.692
The Omec has to die.

08:24.898 --> 08:27.198
I suppose you're right.

08:32.823 --> 08:36.408
We have betrayed
our neighbors,

08:36.460 --> 08:40.378
and so long as that madman
has the power to expose us,

08:40.414 --> 08:43.748
we must obey his commands

08:43.799 --> 08:46.718
for our own survival,

08:46.753 --> 08:48.753
if not Alak's.

08:48.755 --> 08:50.922
Is that poison?

08:50.924 --> 08:53.258
I'll fill a hidden needle

08:53.260 --> 08:55.927
and inject the Omec
during coitus.

08:57.597 --> 08:58.930
Coitus?

08:58.982 --> 09:01.099
It's a human word.

09:01.101 --> 09:03.318
- It means...
- I know what it means.

09:03.353 --> 09:05.770
T'evgin will suffer
cardiac arrest,

09:05.772 --> 09:08.239
leaving no evidence
of foul play.

09:08.275 --> 09:10.658
Well, surely
there's some other way.

09:10.694 --> 09:13.161
My way is effective
and safe.

09:14.781 --> 09:17.082
Rest assured, love,

09:17.117 --> 09:19.334
I will think only of you.

09:21.171 --> 09:24.122
[dramatic music]

09:24.475 --> 09:29.749
_

09:29.784 --> 09:37.790
♪ ♪

09:40.607 --> 09:43.274
Looks like
it's been recently plowed.

09:43.310 --> 09:46.311
According to this,
underground access

09:46.363 --> 09:48.363
is in that barn.

10:00.494 --> 10:02.260
[sniffs]

10:02.295 --> 10:05.330
Ah, that barn smell.
Heh.

10:05.382 --> 10:07.499
You mean manure?

10:07.501 --> 10:09.417
What ever happened
to romance?

10:09.469 --> 10:11.336
I killed it
and ate it.

10:12.506 --> 10:14.172
- [groans]
- Nolan, you okay?

10:14.224 --> 10:16.174
[groans]
Just a headache.

10:16.176 --> 10:18.092
[groans]

10:23.183 --> 10:31.189
♪ ♪

10:50.744 --> 10:53.711
[grunting]

10:55.182 --> 10:56.130
Leave the fingers.

10:56.183 --> 10:58.716
Leave... leave... leave...
Ah, ow!

11:01.304 --> 11:03.137
Come with me.

11:14.067 --> 11:16.367
I don't suppose
I could hang on to my gun?

11:16.403 --> 11:18.203
No.

11:18.238 --> 11:21.122
- Come on, pal.
- George isn't your pal.

11:21.157 --> 11:23.074
Neither am I.

11:23.126 --> 11:26.077
[dramatic music]

11:26.129 --> 11:34.135
♪ ♪

11:35.505 --> 11:37.171
It's amazing.

11:43.230 --> 11:46.097
(George)
You look just like her.

11:46.099 --> 11:47.098
Like who?

11:47.100 --> 11:49.934
The girl from the movies.

11:49.936 --> 11:52.820
What movies?
What are you talking about?

11:52.856 --> 11:54.606
No more talking.

12:01.581 --> 12:09.587
♪ ♪

12:19.866 --> 12:21.799
Niles?

12:21.851 --> 12:23.584
Oh, nuts.

12:24.559 --> 12:26.035
After our
garrison left Defiance,

12:26.134 --> 12:29.485
Viceroy Mercado decided
to lead us back to New York

12:29.537 --> 12:32.071
to provide aid and comfort,
and it was futile.

12:32.123 --> 12:34.156
Before we made Cincinnati,
we were overrun

12:34.158 --> 12:35.541
by refugees streaming west.

12:35.576 --> 12:37.893
They were burned
and bloodied and sick.

12:37.928 --> 12:38.994
They'd lost everything.

12:38.996 --> 12:41.497
It was heartbreaking,
truly.

12:41.549 --> 12:44.166
Ooh, try the Camembert.
Try it. It's divine.

12:46.837 --> 12:48.337
We offered them
what little comfort we could.

12:48.339 --> 12:50.339
Of course,
we shared their provisions.

12:50.391 --> 12:51.340
Of course.

12:51.392 --> 12:54.727
Yeah, that's right.
Thanks, Paul.

12:54.762 --> 12:57.062
Many of the refugees
joined us as we headed north

12:57.098 --> 12:59.682
up to Arrowhead
to resupply.

12:59.734 --> 13:02.735
Well, I mean,
obviously you made it here,

13:02.770 --> 13:04.820
but what happened
to everyone else?

13:04.855 --> 13:06.739
We hit raiders
outside Detroit.

13:06.774 --> 13:08.574
I escaped,

13:08.609 --> 13:10.275
but Mercado and the others...
they weren't so lucky.

13:10.327 --> 13:12.194
- Doubt it was luck.
- Nolan.

13:12.246 --> 13:14.413
Come on,
I wanna hear this.

13:14.448 --> 13:17.032
I made my way here
to Arrowhead alone,

13:17.068 --> 13:19.785
found the entrance,
but I didn't know the passcode.

13:19.837 --> 13:21.203
Would have died
from the elements

13:21.238 --> 13:24.206
had it not been for an angel
who came to my rescue.

13:24.208 --> 13:26.875
An angel named George.

13:26.927 --> 13:30.012
- I'm not really an angel.
- That's a matter of opinion.

13:30.047 --> 13:31.880
(Pottinger) George here
brought me inside,

13:31.882 --> 13:35.350
and he and his fellow Biomen
kept Station Arrowhead

13:35.386 --> 13:37.553
humming along
since the Pale Wars ended.

13:37.588 --> 13:39.555
It's a remarkable place.

13:39.607 --> 13:41.023
It's completely
self-sustaining.

13:41.058 --> 13:43.225
It was built as a refuge
for the government elite

13:43.277 --> 13:44.526
in case the world
went to hell.

13:44.562 --> 13:46.395
There's a fully stocked
seed vault,

13:46.397 --> 13:48.480
functional rain chamber.

13:48.532 --> 13:51.734
There's even DNA samples
of old-world animals.

13:51.736 --> 13:54.203
Cows and goats,
cats and dogs.

13:54.238 --> 13:57.906
I had a dog once.
He only had three legs.

13:57.908 --> 13:59.241
I know, Georgie, I know,

13:59.243 --> 14:00.876
but he's
in a much better place now.

14:00.911 --> 14:02.461
- Isn't he?
- Mm.

14:09.253 --> 14:11.553
This is the last
of the stuff.

14:23.150 --> 14:25.434
[groans]

14:25.486 --> 14:26.935
Guilty conscience
eating at you?

14:26.937 --> 14:29.238
It's a headache.

14:29.273 --> 14:30.939
[sighs]

14:31.942 --> 14:33.408
It's nothing.

14:33.444 --> 14:35.944
Look at this.

14:38.666 --> 14:40.415
So? It's just part
of a boom box.

14:40.451 --> 14:42.618
The Arch was full
of old radio junk.

14:43.788 --> 14:46.121
Look at these burns
and how the edges

14:46.123 --> 14:47.623
are blown out
from the inside.

14:47.675 --> 14:50.425
This radio was
the casing for the bomb.

14:50.461 --> 14:52.628
Let's see if we can
get a print off it.

14:54.181 --> 14:55.848
[classical music]

14:55.883 --> 15:00.769
So it's just you here
underground?

15:00.805 --> 15:03.522
With your four
color-coordinated Biomen.

15:03.557 --> 15:05.974
Your own little slice of heaven,
if you ask me.

15:05.976 --> 15:08.610
(Pottinger)
Nolan's sarcasm notwithstanding,

15:08.646 --> 15:12.731
yes, I have built quite
the pleasant life for myself.

15:12.783 --> 15:15.033
I read. I write.

15:15.069 --> 15:16.485
I farm.

15:16.537 --> 15:17.820
I've even been known
to dabble in carpentry

15:17.822 --> 15:18.821
from time to time.

15:18.823 --> 15:21.323
[laughs, coughs]

15:21.325 --> 15:24.993
- You all right?
- [coughs]

15:25.045 --> 15:28.080
I'm glad you're happy.

15:28.132 --> 15:31.300
I appreciate that,
Amanda, I do.

15:31.335 --> 15:33.302
I've missed you.

15:33.337 --> 15:35.771
I've missed you
an awful lot.

15:35.806 --> 15:38.640
[chuckles]

15:38.676 --> 15:42.561
Well, before I start
blubbing all over myself,

15:42.596 --> 15:44.179
let's get to it.

15:44.231 --> 15:46.648
I can't imagine
this is a social visit.

15:46.684 --> 15:49.184
What you need?
Food? Building materials?

15:49.220 --> 15:50.185
Guns.

15:50.221 --> 15:51.687
Since the E-Rep fell apart,

15:51.689 --> 15:54.239
the Votanis Collective
has been growing in strength.

15:54.275 --> 15:56.742
They blew up the Arch.

15:56.777 --> 15:59.528
Good Lord.
It's gone completely?

15:59.530 --> 16:01.413
Yes.

16:01.448 --> 16:03.582
I can only imagine how deeply
it affects you, Amanda.

16:03.617 --> 16:05.868
Why did you let me prattle on
about myself so much?

16:05.870 --> 16:08.453
- You were kind of on a roll.
- [chuckles]

16:08.505 --> 16:10.539
I'm afraid I do still rather
enjoy the sound of my own voice.

16:10.541 --> 16:12.374
Your request is granted.

16:12.376 --> 16:14.960
Ringo, show our friends
to the armory.

16:15.012 --> 16:16.378
Yeah?

16:16.380 --> 16:17.779
Let them take as many weapons

16:17.815 --> 16:19.014
as they can fit
into their roller.

16:19.049 --> 16:20.933
All right, then.

16:20.968 --> 16:23.685
Niles, I can't
thank you enough.

16:23.721 --> 16:25.687
My pleasure.
Oh, Amanda, Amanda.

16:29.360 --> 16:31.443
Could I have a word
in private?

16:33.781 --> 16:36.648
I'm fine. Go.

16:36.700 --> 16:38.867
Nolan doesn't trust me.

16:38.903 --> 16:40.702
I don't trust anyone.

16:40.738 --> 16:42.070
Do you wanna
blow this?

16:42.072 --> 16:43.672
I'm not leaving you alone
with this guy.

16:43.707 --> 16:45.040
I can handle him.
I mean it.

16:45.075 --> 16:46.792
Go.

16:49.463 --> 16:50.963
I'll be back
in ten minutes.

16:50.998 --> 16:52.631
(Pottinger)
Very good.

16:58.589 --> 17:00.255
[elevator dings]

17:01.976 --> 17:04.926
[romantic music]

17:04.979 --> 17:08.430
♪ ♪

17:08.464 --> 17:10.299
[Amanda sighs]

17:10.334 --> 17:13.068
Is this a conversation
or a seduction?

17:13.103 --> 17:16.570
Hopefully both.

17:16.607 --> 17:18.490
I've been thinking
about six months ago,

17:18.525 --> 17:21.042
when I left Defiance
for New York,

17:21.078 --> 17:23.444
how you refused
to join me.

17:23.497 --> 17:25.614
You know I care about you...

17:25.616 --> 17:27.199
No, no, no, no, no.
It's-it's all right.

17:27.251 --> 17:29.451
I completely understand.

17:29.486 --> 17:32.037
There were
so many distractions.

17:32.089 --> 17:34.506
Protecting Defiance,
rebuilding the E-Rep,

17:34.541 --> 17:36.792
fighting the V.C.

17:37.962 --> 17:40.963
This period of solitude

17:40.965 --> 17:45.434
has... has clarified certain...

17:45.469 --> 17:48.470
primal sanities.

17:48.522 --> 17:52.858
You and I are special.

17:52.893 --> 17:57.646
We're bound together in a deep
and fundamental manner.

17:57.698 --> 18:02.117
But Eve could not truly
join her Adam...

18:02.152 --> 18:04.903
until...

18:04.955 --> 18:08.040
the perfect Eden
revealed itself.

18:10.210 --> 18:11.793
And now it has.

18:11.829 --> 18:14.212
Amanda, what would you say
to the idea

18:14.248 --> 18:18.667
of staying on here
permanently?

18:18.669 --> 18:22.838
♪ Oh, I want the truth
to be said ♪

18:33.400 --> 18:35.400
[groans]

18:37.771 --> 18:39.771
[Nolan sighs]

18:41.725 --> 18:43.908
We getting the band
back together?

18:51.507 --> 18:54.275
[clears throat]

18:54.310 --> 18:56.159
I didn't mean to intrude.

18:56.195 --> 18:59.780
Surprising an Omec
is a dangerous pursuit.

18:59.832 --> 19:01.999
Forgive me.

19:02.034 --> 19:05.335
I came
for your culture lessons.

19:05.371 --> 19:08.839
We never specified
a time.

19:08.874 --> 19:11.708
And that, I think,
is a lie.

19:11.760 --> 19:13.126
[chuckles]

19:13.128 --> 19:16.680
Partially, yes.

19:16.715 --> 19:19.049
My husband is in a mood,

19:19.101 --> 19:22.519
and I was anxious
for some more pleasant company.

19:24.390 --> 19:28.025
Something to take my mind
off the Arch.

19:28.060 --> 19:31.194
The Gateway Arch
is a human monument.

19:31.230 --> 19:34.648
Why should a <i>Shanje</i>
such as yourself

19:34.700 --> 19:36.984
care about its destruction?

19:39.989 --> 19:42.739
My son Alak
ran the radio station

19:42.791 --> 19:44.658
from the top
of the Arch.

19:44.710 --> 19:48.161
It meant more to him
than anything else.

19:51.216 --> 19:52.799
I see.

19:55.471 --> 19:57.838
Would you care
for something to drink?

20:01.727 --> 20:03.143
Haven't you done enough
for Defiance?

20:03.178 --> 20:05.646
I can't hide underground
and watch my town burn.

20:05.681 --> 20:07.180
You know that.

20:08.734 --> 20:11.685
We're meant to be together.
Yeah?

20:11.687 --> 20:13.954
I belong to you,

20:13.989 --> 20:16.106
and you belong to me.

20:19.194 --> 20:20.160
Amanda, you're mine.

20:20.195 --> 20:22.079
[gasps]

20:22.114 --> 20:23.864
What?

20:27.036 --> 20:30.120
"You're mine," that's what
my attacker said in New York...

20:30.172 --> 20:31.705
Oh, I'm so sorry.
Of course...

20:31.757 --> 20:33.040
Of course you told me
all about that night.

20:33.042 --> 20:34.624
I'm so sorry, okay?
It was just...

20:34.677 --> 20:37.511
It was an unfortunate choice
of words.

20:37.546 --> 20:39.680
No, no, no.
I'm sorry.

20:39.715 --> 20:41.264
I'm sorry, you think
you're over something,

20:41.300 --> 20:44.885
and then it just comes back
at you in unexpected ways.

20:44.937 --> 20:48.605
Uh, do you have
any Scotch?

20:51.560 --> 20:52.726
[bottles clink]

20:52.778 --> 20:55.979
Real Scotch. That's bourbon.
I checked earlier.

20:56.031 --> 20:58.031
Of course you did.
I'll be right back.

20:58.067 --> 21:01.034
[dramatic music]

21:01.070 --> 21:09.076
♪ ♪

21:12.414 --> 21:17.584
So you have no idea whether
your son is alive or not?

21:17.636 --> 21:21.671
I can only pray to Rayetso
for his safe return.

21:21.724 --> 21:25.726
I, too, am no stranger
to loss of family.

21:25.761 --> 21:27.928
I'm sorry.

21:27.930 --> 21:30.764
I have learned to find solace
in our great works.

21:30.766 --> 21:35.185
The most enduring are
about finding meaning in loss.

21:35.237 --> 21:38.071
I spent many long nights
on my ship

21:38.107 --> 21:41.575
considering what
the Indogene had done to us.

21:41.610 --> 21:43.994
I could not help but wonder
if we had not brought

21:44.029 --> 21:46.913
tragedy upon ourselves.

21:46.949 --> 21:49.616
Death breeds death.

21:51.954 --> 21:56.289
The greatest Omec opera
was about that very thing.

21:56.441 --> 21:59.221
_

22:00.295 --> 22:03.130
Yes.
[chuckles]

22:03.132 --> 22:05.132
It's my favorite.

22:06.769 --> 22:09.719
[humming tune]

22:09.772 --> 22:17.778
♪ ♪

22:23.318 --> 22:26.286
[T'evgin joins humming tune]

22:26.321 --> 22:32.209
♪ ♪

22:32.244 --> 22:35.245
[giggles]

22:35.297 --> 22:39.132
Why have you really come here,
my lovely little show-off?

22:39.168 --> 22:41.418
I want the truth.

22:41.470 --> 22:44.888
The entire truth.

22:44.923 --> 22:47.274
Isn't it obvious?

22:47.509 --> 22:51.846
_

22:55.851 --> 22:58.852
[sensual music]

22:58.854 --> 23:00.020
♪ ♪

23:00.072 --> 23:02.856
[moaning]

23:39.361 --> 23:42.362
[T'evgin snarling]

24:08.423 --> 24:11.424
[panting]

24:13.312 --> 24:15.762
Would you like
to go again?

24:21.153 --> 24:23.153
[chuckles]

24:31.957 --> 24:33.790
[groans]

24:33.792 --> 24:36.710
You took a nice shot there.

24:36.762 --> 24:38.545
Turn your head to the light,
so I can check your pupils.

24:38.597 --> 24:40.547
[groans]

24:40.599 --> 24:41.848
Do you know your name?

24:41.884 --> 24:45.068
Yeah, Joshua Nolan.

24:45.103 --> 24:48.054
Good. I'm Samir.

24:48.106 --> 24:50.640
Do you remember
what happened to you?

24:50.692 --> 24:54.478
Oh, Bioman took
a cheap shot.

24:54.480 --> 24:55.979
You a medic?

24:56.031 --> 24:58.648
I was a veterinarian...

24:58.700 --> 25:00.400
before New York
got destroyed.

25:00.452 --> 25:02.402
But now I work on humans
and Sensoths

25:02.454 --> 25:03.653
and everything
in between.

25:03.655 --> 25:05.071
Any nausea?

25:05.123 --> 25:08.241
No, no, I'm fine.
Hard head.

25:08.293 --> 25:10.577
Yeah, that cut on your head,
how did you get that?

25:10.629 --> 25:13.997
Long, complicated story.

25:17.085 --> 25:18.502
[sighs]

25:19.671 --> 25:22.506
Uh, that's locked,
by the way.

25:22.508 --> 25:24.007
[sighs]

25:24.059 --> 25:26.426
How many Biomen
on site?

25:26.478 --> 25:28.345
Oh, just the Fab Four.

25:28.380 --> 25:31.181
Yeah?
You have people with you?

25:31.233 --> 25:33.350
Used to.

25:33.352 --> 25:36.019
30 of us
from New York.

25:36.071 --> 25:39.022
We managed to escape after
the Great Terraforming Disaster.

25:39.024 --> 25:40.774
Um, after a few months,
we met up

25:40.826 --> 25:42.025
with Pottinger's soldiers
on the road.

25:42.077 --> 25:44.694
I mean, E-Rep, we thought
they'd keep us safe.

25:44.746 --> 25:48.031
Until Pottinger
just went nuts.

25:50.502 --> 25:52.869
I mean, he put a bullet through
his commanding officer's head

25:52.921 --> 25:55.171
and then declared himself
in charge.

25:55.207 --> 25:57.707
Some of us tried
to stop him.

25:57.759 --> 26:00.510
People died.

26:00.546 --> 26:03.296
After that, Pottinger knew that
none of us trusted him,

26:03.348 --> 26:06.132
so to keep people in line,

26:06.184 --> 26:08.885
he forced me to wire

26:08.937 --> 26:10.604
a dead-man switch
to his chest.

26:10.639 --> 26:12.389
You're shitting me.

26:12.391 --> 26:13.390
If Pottinger's heart
stops beating,

26:13.392 --> 26:14.558
it triggers a bomb.

26:14.560 --> 26:17.060
What kind of a bomb?

26:17.112 --> 26:18.562
Uh, you remember Portland?

26:18.614 --> 26:20.564
Yeah, I've seen the crater.

26:23.035 --> 26:25.035
He wired himself
to a singularity bomb?

26:25.070 --> 26:26.736
Yeah.

26:26.738 --> 26:30.240
If he dies, this whole place
gets sucked into a wormhole.

26:31.743 --> 26:33.877
(Nolan)
We gotta get out of here now.

26:37.499 --> 26:40.800
Put that down.

26:40.836 --> 26:42.552
Where's Nolan?

26:42.588 --> 26:44.137
In the armory.

26:44.172 --> 26:45.589
Can you take me to him?

26:45.641 --> 26:46.723
No.

26:48.760 --> 26:51.928
George,
why is that door padlocked?

26:53.515 --> 26:56.850
[sighs]
It's-it's private.

27:00.105 --> 27:01.855
In the elevator,
you said I reminded you

27:01.907 --> 27:03.156
of the girl in the movies.

27:03.191 --> 27:05.659
Who is she?
What did you mean?

27:07.079 --> 27:09.446
[footsteps approaching]

27:09.448 --> 27:11.031
Thank you, George.
That'll be all.

27:11.083 --> 27:12.032
I should stay.

27:12.084 --> 27:13.700
I think
she might try to hurt you.

27:13.752 --> 27:14.834
Oh.

27:14.870 --> 27:16.836
I don't think
she's happy here.

27:16.872 --> 27:19.623
You're very perceptive,
George.

27:19.625 --> 27:22.092
Your boss said something to me
that reminded me

27:22.127 --> 27:23.793
of a bad thing that happened,
so, yes,

27:23.845 --> 27:25.762
I'm not happy.

27:25.797 --> 27:28.932
But it's nothing an old-world
single malt can't fix.

27:28.967 --> 27:32.052
I can wait
outside the doors.

27:32.104 --> 27:35.639
What is he, a Bioman
or a jealous girlfriend?

27:35.691 --> 27:37.140
Go see to the dishes,
George.

27:37.192 --> 27:39.142
I shan't ask you again.

27:39.194 --> 27:40.644
Okay.

27:40.696 --> 27:41.645
Rather like a Labrador,
isn't he?

27:41.697 --> 27:43.146
[chuckles]

27:44.733 --> 27:46.900
So I've been thinking
about your offer.

27:46.952 --> 27:48.568
I'm willing to stay,

27:48.620 --> 27:50.320
but there's a price.

27:50.322 --> 27:52.038
Go on.

27:58.296 --> 28:00.747
I'll do anything
to keep Defiance safe.

28:03.635 --> 28:07.003
You offered us a roller
filled with weapons,

28:07.005 --> 28:09.255
but that's
not nearly enough.

28:09.307 --> 28:12.842
I propose
we send Nolan back

28:12.844 --> 28:16.062
with the weapons,
he returns with a caravan

28:16.098 --> 28:18.982
to haul everything
back to Defiance.

28:19.017 --> 28:21.401
- Everything?
- Mm-hmm.

28:21.436 --> 28:25.321
Every single weapon
in your armory,

28:25.357 --> 28:27.857
down to the last firecracker.

28:27.859 --> 28:30.860
Defiance gets the guns,

28:30.912 --> 28:33.196
and you get me.

28:42.841 --> 28:45.258
All right, jackass.

28:45.293 --> 28:46.710
Open the door.

28:46.712 --> 28:48.178
The screening room.
Now!

28:48.213 --> 28:49.713
Amanda, please.

28:49.715 --> 28:50.764
[gun cocks]

28:50.799 --> 28:53.049
Open it, or I open you.

28:56.638 --> 28:58.888
All right, all right.

29:01.026 --> 29:03.943
Something you must know
about me first.

29:03.979 --> 29:06.112
I'm not well.

29:06.148 --> 29:08.782
The abuse I suffered
when I was...

29:08.817 --> 29:10.567
attacked by Votans
at my boarding school...

29:10.619 --> 29:12.619
Shut up! Move!

29:14.122 --> 29:15.238
Okay.

29:16.942 --> 29:18.792
Okay.

29:26.818 --> 29:29.836
How do you like it, hmm?

29:29.888 --> 29:31.721
My special place.

29:36.845 --> 29:38.678
(Amanda)
What is all this stuff?

29:41.266 --> 29:44.017
This mask.
This flashlight.

29:45.270 --> 29:46.436
Now listen to me carefully.

29:46.488 --> 29:47.937
When I love someone,

29:47.989 --> 29:51.191
I become completely and utterly
enthralled with them,

29:51.243 --> 29:52.826
their tragedies,
everything.

29:52.861 --> 29:55.495
What's on these video chips?

29:55.530 --> 29:59.115
Uh, just all
the video diaries of...

30:04.005 --> 30:05.855
Play this one
with my name on it.

30:05.891 --> 30:08.558
Now. Play it!
Now!

30:12.848 --> 30:14.380
Okay.

30:15.634 --> 30:16.633
[sighs]
Oh, damn.

30:16.635 --> 30:17.934
[clears throat]

30:28.947 --> 30:32.682
Such ethereal beauty.

30:32.717 --> 30:34.184
[cries]

30:40.325 --> 30:42.292
I can't believe
I didn't see this.

30:46.548 --> 30:49.332
Before me it was Connor.

30:49.384 --> 30:51.417
Ah, we were school chums.

30:51.469 --> 30:53.586
He protected me
when the Votan attacked.

30:53.638 --> 30:56.673
He saved me.

30:56.675 --> 30:58.174
I loved him.

30:58.226 --> 30:59.259
And then what?

30:59.311 --> 31:01.578
Then you followed him
to New York?

31:01.613 --> 31:04.013
Hmm, yes.

31:04.015 --> 31:06.850
Connor didn't want
to see me.

31:06.902 --> 31:11.271
So sometimes I would follow
people who were close to him,

31:11.323 --> 31:13.189
so they might lead me
to him.

31:13.191 --> 31:14.774
Like that night
in Central Park

31:14.826 --> 31:16.576
when I was attacked?

31:16.611 --> 31:18.528
Yeah, yeah,
I saw what happened,

31:18.580 --> 31:20.864
and I wanted
to stop it, okay?

31:20.866 --> 31:22.699
But I froze.

31:22.701 --> 31:24.617
I was a coward.

31:24.669 --> 31:26.703
But after your attacker left,

31:26.705 --> 31:28.621
I wanted to help you.

31:28.673 --> 31:31.958
But how could I justify
being there, Amanda?

31:32.010 --> 31:34.260
In that moment,
all my guilt, all my shame,

31:34.296 --> 31:36.679
my self-hatred,
it just exploded into a rage.

31:36.715 --> 31:39.299
But I chased
after your attacker,

31:39.351 --> 31:40.300
and I caught him.

31:40.352 --> 31:41.718
I bashed in his skull,

31:41.720 --> 31:44.220
and I rolled his body
into the the river, for you.

31:44.222 --> 31:45.955
Yet you kept
his mask and flashlight?

31:45.991 --> 31:48.224
They're replicas!

31:48.260 --> 31:50.994
(Amanda)
Replicas? Bullshit!

31:51.029 --> 31:53.663
Come on, Amanda.

31:53.698 --> 31:55.815
Please put down the gun.

31:57.869 --> 32:00.370
That's it.
Pass it to me.

32:00.405 --> 32:02.538
Okay, if you shot me,

32:02.574 --> 32:05.041
the entire station
would've exploded.

32:06.328 --> 32:08.161
- [gunshot]
- Ah!

32:08.213 --> 32:09.162
[groaning]

32:09.214 --> 32:12.165
[ominous music]

32:12.217 --> 32:16.085
♪ ♪

32:16.087 --> 32:18.237
Looks like
we're all still here.

32:20.283 --> 32:21.534
[grunts]

32:22.086 --> 32:24.920
- Let's move.
- I'm right behind you.

32:24.972 --> 32:27.573
You're not supposed
to open the door.

32:32.913 --> 32:34.179
Okay, he's, uh...

32:34.231 --> 32:35.347
he's really new here.

32:35.399 --> 32:38.517
He doesn't know...
[grunts]

32:38.569 --> 32:40.102
[grunting]

32:48.996 --> 32:51.363
[Nolan groans]

33:06.380 --> 33:07.713
[pants]

33:07.715 --> 33:10.015
[groaning]

33:13.137 --> 33:15.137
[screaming]

33:37.578 --> 33:40.079
[Ringo growling]

33:47.338 --> 33:49.588
Nice thinking,
doggie doctor.

33:49.590 --> 33:51.557
[growls]

33:52.593 --> 33:54.343
[gunshot in distance]

33:54.395 --> 33:55.928
Amanda.
Come on!

33:57.314 --> 33:59.598
Please, stop.

33:59.650 --> 34:01.934
If you kill me,
we will all die.

34:01.936 --> 34:03.652
I wanna hear you
say it.

34:03.687 --> 34:05.771
Admit what you did!

34:05.773 --> 34:06.939
Say it!

34:06.941 --> 34:09.775
Please, Amanda...

34:09.777 --> 34:11.159
don't do this.

34:11.195 --> 34:14.862
- [gunshot]
- [screams]

34:14.915 --> 34:17.866
- Say it.
- [screams]

34:19.587 --> 34:20.668
[gunshot]

34:20.704 --> 34:22.920
- [screams]
- Say it.

34:24.592 --> 34:27.042
- I love you!
- Say it!

34:28.846 --> 34:29.844
[gunshot]

34:29.880 --> 34:31.630
[screams]

34:33.884 --> 34:35.601
Say it!

34:37.471 --> 34:39.471
[groans]

34:49.233 --> 34:51.567
Amanda, no!

34:51.619 --> 34:53.118
- Samir!
- I'm on it!

34:53.154 --> 34:54.570
Keep him alive.
Don't let him die.

34:54.621 --> 34:56.871
Come on.

34:56.907 --> 34:59.658
Hey. Hey.

35:03.164 --> 35:04.163
He raped me.

35:04.165 --> 35:06.331
Come on, come on.
No, no, no, no, no.

35:06.333 --> 35:09.251
[crying]
It was him.

35:14.775 --> 35:15.724
[alarm blaring]

35:15.759 --> 35:17.392
He's dead.

35:17.428 --> 35:20.395
[dramatic music]

35:20.431 --> 35:21.980
♪ ♪

35:22.016 --> 35:24.683
(Nolan)
We gotta get out of here.

35:24.735 --> 35:26.235
Amanda, come on!

35:26.270 --> 35:29.021
Hey! We gotta go!
Come on!

35:36.831 --> 35:41.283
♪ ♪

35:55.099 --> 35:58.116
Faster! Faster!
Come on!

36:03.607 --> 36:05.607
Pretty.

36:53.108 --> 37:01.114
♪ ♪

37:04.336 --> 37:07.420
Ah, you're awake.

37:09.291 --> 37:11.458
I made some pancakes.

37:11.460 --> 37:14.177
I got the ingredients
from the NeedWant bazaar.

37:14.212 --> 37:16.045
Oh, thank you.

37:16.098 --> 37:17.046
I hope you like them.

37:17.099 --> 37:18.431
Oh.

37:24.189 --> 37:26.556
[laughs]

37:26.608 --> 37:28.608
Enjoy them
while they're hot.

37:34.483 --> 37:37.450
Oh, your needle.

37:41.406 --> 37:43.740
I suppose we should discuss
the poison.

37:46.244 --> 37:47.710
Poison?

37:47.746 --> 37:49.829
You're not
the first Castithan concubine

37:49.881 --> 37:52.465
that has attempted
to murder me.

37:52.501 --> 37:55.885
Your people know nothing
about my physiology,

37:55.921 --> 37:59.556
and that's exactly
the way I like it.

37:59.591 --> 38:05.178
I have lived
for many, many centuries,

38:05.230 --> 38:06.679
and the longer
my people live,

38:06.681 --> 38:09.015
the more difficult
we are to kill.

38:10.852 --> 38:14.237
So why do you
want me dead?

38:15.907 --> 38:18.825
Actually, I don't.

38:18.860 --> 38:20.693
And I don't want
to be killed,

38:20.695 --> 38:23.079
so I guess that puts us
on the same page.

38:23.114 --> 38:25.365
As the humans say.

38:25.367 --> 38:27.367
So why the poison?

38:31.173 --> 38:34.374
I lied earlier.

38:34.376 --> 38:37.277
I know exactly
where my son is.

38:37.312 --> 38:40.813
The Votanis Collective
have taken him hostage.

38:40.849 --> 38:43.416
They ordered me
to kill you,

38:43.451 --> 38:45.118
or his life
would be forfeit.

38:45.153 --> 38:47.103
What will you tell them?

38:47.138 --> 38:49.722
The truth.

38:49.774 --> 38:51.441
I have failed.

38:51.476 --> 38:52.892
Will you try again?

38:52.944 --> 38:55.228
Do I have any chance
of success?

38:55.230 --> 38:57.564
[chuckles]
I'm afraid not.

38:59.201 --> 39:01.284
What shall you do?

39:06.324 --> 39:09.125
In my entire life,

39:09.160 --> 39:12.128
no man has ever
made a meal for me.

39:13.498 --> 39:15.131
I feel
I should thank you.

39:20.088 --> 39:22.639
[laughs]

39:22.674 --> 39:24.057
[giggles]

39:30.265 --> 39:32.849
You know
whose badge that is.

39:32.901 --> 39:34.484
Of course I do.

39:46.948 --> 39:49.032
I miss him too.

39:50.085 --> 39:51.618
- I loved Tommy.
- Shut up!

39:52.837 --> 39:55.288
You don't kill
what you love!

39:55.340 --> 39:56.539
[gasps]

39:56.591 --> 39:59.876
It wasn't me.
It was the machine!

40:01.846 --> 40:04.847
Is it a machine holding a knife
to my neck right now?

40:07.552 --> 40:10.553
[groaning]

40:11.806 --> 40:14.807
[screaming]

40:20.699 --> 40:22.282
[knife clatters]

40:22.317 --> 40:24.367
[groans]

40:24.402 --> 40:26.486
What the <i>chup?</i>

40:38.967 --> 40:40.500
Nolan, I'm so sorry.

40:40.502 --> 40:41.884
Don't.

40:41.920 --> 40:44.470
If I hadn't killed Pottinger,
we would have those weapons

40:44.506 --> 40:46.422
to fight the V.C.

40:46.474 --> 40:50.009
Yeah, possible.

40:50.061 --> 40:52.762
Also possible that
killing Pottinger saved us

40:52.814 --> 40:54.981
from being murdered
by Biomen

40:55.016 --> 40:58.935
or, in your case,
something much worse.

41:02.407 --> 41:03.356
[kisses]

41:03.408 --> 41:06.609
What's that for?

41:06.661 --> 41:10.196
For being
one of the good guys.

41:10.248 --> 41:12.782
- [groans]
- Nolan? Nolan!

41:12.834 --> 41:15.368
Nolan!
He's bleeding!

41:15.370 --> 41:17.036
Get me a stick!

41:20.625 --> 41:22.592
[groaning]

41:22.627 --> 41:23.943
(Samir) The blood's coming
from his head wound.

41:23.978 --> 41:25.762
- What caused it?
- Some kind of Votan tech.

41:25.797 --> 41:27.380
- More specific!
- I don't know!

41:27.382 --> 41:28.798
You need to make
an educated guess

41:28.850 --> 41:31.134
because whatever's
inside this man's head

41:31.186 --> 41:34.053
is killing him.

41:34.105 --> 41:36.556
[groaning]

41:38.226 --> 41:40.777
What's wrong with you?

41:40.812 --> 41:42.812
[gasping]

41:45.483 --> 41:47.233
Help me.

41:48.670 --> 41:50.670
Please.

